    <div class="calc-layout">
      <div class="calc-main">
        <h1>🎨 Paint Calculator</h1>
        <p class="calc-intro">Calculate exactly how many litres of paint you need for your room.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>Room width (m)</label><input type="number" id="pin-ancho" placeholder="4" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
            <div><label>Room length (m)</label><input type="number" id="pin-largo" placeholder="5" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
          </div>
          <label>Wall height (m)</label>
          <input type="number" id="pin-alto" placeholder="2.5" oninput="calcPaint()">
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>Number of doors</label><input type="number" id="pin-puertas" placeholder="1" value="1" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
            <div><label>Number of windows</label><input type="number" id="pin-ventanas" placeholder="1" value="1" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>Number of coats</label><input type="number" id="pin-manos" placeholder="2" value="2" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
            <div><label>Coverage (m²/litre)</label><input type="number" id="pin-rend" placeholder="10" value="10" oninput="calcPaint()"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-box" id="pin-res">Enter the room dimensions</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>How to calculate paint needed</h2>
          <p>Calculate the total wall area, subtract the area of doors and windows, then divide by the paint coverage (m² per litre) and multiply by the number of coats. Always add 10% extra for wastage and touch-ups.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How many coats of paint do I need?</summary>
            <p>For light colours over white, 2 coats are usually enough. For dark colours or covering stains, you may need 3 coats.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is the coverage of standard paint?</summary>
            <p>Most standard interior paints cover 10–12 m² per litre per coat. Textured or masonry paints typically cover less — check the tin for exact coverage.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Should I buy extra paint?</summary>
            <p>Yes, always buy 10–15% more than calculated. Keep some spare for future touch-ups — matching paint from a different batch can be difficult.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
